        <div class="post-text">Except for manufacturing flaws, hardware fails due to being under load for a period of time. More stress (in the case of most hardware, heat) increases the chance of failure. Hardware &quot;does&quot; care what software is running; if that's not the case, I invite you to run the folding@home GPU client, Furmark, or an unpatched release copy of Starcraft 2 stuck on the title screen, plus Prime for CPU tests, for days on end and see how confident you are in Furmark not having artifacts/Prime or folding@home not returning corrupt results.</div>
        
